HEADWORD: Shillelah
<hw>Shil*le"lah</hw> }</mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <def>An oaken sapling or cudgel; any cudgel; -- so called
from <xex>Shillelagh</xex>, a place in Ireland of that name famous for
its oaks.</def> <mark>[Irish]</mark> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>shillaly</asp>, and <asp>shillely</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

